      $( [8-Sep-2010] $) $( [14-May-2003] $)

    $( An ordered pair theorem for nonnegative integers.  Theorem 17.3 of
       [Quine] p. 124.  We can represent an ordered pair of nonnegative
       integers ` A ` and ` B ` by ` ( ( ( A + B ) x. ( A + B ) ) + B ) ` .  If
       two such ordered pairs are equal, their first elements are equal and
       their second elements are equal.  Contrast this ordered pair
       representation with the standard one ~ df-op that works for any set.
       (Contributed by Raph Levien, 10-Dec-2002.  Proof shortened by Scott
       Fenton, 7-Sep-2010.) $)
    nn0opthi $p |- ( ( ( ( A + B ) x. ( A + B ) ) + B ) =
            ( ( ( C + D ) x. ( C + D ) ) + D ) <-> ( A = C /\ B = D ) ) $=
      ( caddc co cmul wceq wne clt nn0addcli nn0rei nn0opthlem2 opreq12d nn0cni
      wbr wa wo lttri2i necomd jaoi sylbi necon4i opreq1d eqtr4d mulcli addcani
      id sylib opreq2d addcan2i jca opreq12 simpr impbii ) ABIJZUTKJZBIJZCDIJZV
      CKJZDIJZLZACLZBDLZUAZVFVGVHVFUTCBIJZLVGVFUTVCVJUTVCVBVEUTVCMUTVCNTZVCUTNT
      ZUBVBVEMZUTVCUTABEFOZPVCCDGHOZPUCVKVMVLVKVEVBABVCDEFVOHQUDCDUTBGHVNFQUEUF
      UGZVFBDCIVFVBVADIJZLVHVFVBVEVQVFULVFVAVDDIVFUTVCUTVCKVPVPRUHUIVABDUTUTUTV
      NSZVRUJBFSZDHSUKUMZUNUIACBAESCGSVSUOUMVTUPVIVAVDBDIVIUTVCUTVCKACBDIUQZWAR
      VGVHURRUS $.
      $( [8-Sep-2010] $) $( [10-Dec-2002] $)

    $( An ordered pair theorem for nonnegative integers.  Theorem 17.3 of
